				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\nu $\end{document} is the kinematic viscosity and η\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\eta $\end{document} the magnetic resistivity, plays a critical role for SSD action and we provide a more detailed account of the theoretical concepts in Sect. 3. It was first suggested by Petrovay and Szakaly (1993) that this dynamo instability may be the origin of the weak IN fields.

