According to Kazantsev’s model, the amplification occurs at the timescale of the turbulent eddy turnover time, which is very short in comparison to the timescales required for the amplification of the large-scale field. In the kinematic growth phase, when the magnetic fluctuations are still weak, the structures generated have the thickness around the resistive scale, but are curved up to the scale of the turbulent eddies. Hence, the peak in the magnetic power spectrum is at the resistive scale, but all scales grow with the same growth rate. At scales larger than the resistive scale, a positive power law of k∝3/2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
